div.p:
These meetings took place on the afternoon of July 12, the morning and afternoon of July 13, and the morning and afternoon of July 14. Mr. Nash himself attended during a part of four of the five sessions. Other New Zealand officials who attended were:
Mr. J. P. D. Johnsen, of the Department of Commerce of New Zealand (an official of the New Zealand customs organization);
Dr. Sutch, Economic Adviser to Mr. Nash;
Mr. J. W. Collins, Trade Commissioner of New Zealand for Eastern United States and Canada;
Mr. W. J. Stevenson, Customs Expert for New Zealand in the United States.
